WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:35.493 --> 00:39.288
WOMAN [OVER TV]: Much more than
just a series of small, isolated incidents...

00:39.456 --> 00:43.667
...it's now apparent that an organized
criminal element is at work.

00:43.835 --> 00:46.545
And at the moment, business is good.

00:46.713 --> 00:49.798
So good, in fact,
that there appear to be no eyewitnesses...

00:49.966 --> 00:51.759
...to any of these crimes.

00:51.926 --> 00:54.303
With complaints ranging
from purse-snatching...

00:54.471 --> 00:55.971
...to breaking and entering...

00:56.139 --> 00:58.265
...police switchboards
have been swamped...

00:58.433 --> 01:01.060
...with the angry voices
of more and more citizens...

01:01.227 --> 01:04.313
...who have fallen prey
to the recent surge of crime...

01:04.480 --> 01:06.190
...that continues to plague the city.

01:21.456 --> 01:26.335
Instead of getting better,
things have actually gotten worse.

01:26.503 --> 01:28.962
Even more alarming is the baffling...

01:29.130 --> 01:32.758
...and often bizarre nature
of these crimes.

01:33.676 --> 01:36.345
Merchandise
of every size and description...

01:36.513 --> 01:38.722
...from skateboards to stereo systems...

01:38.890 --> 01:41.850
...has been disappearing
from store shelves and storage areas...

01:42.018 --> 01:44.520
...at an alarming rate.

01:44.979 --> 01:46.772
MAN:
Aah...

01:47.524 --> 01:51.360
Even the victims themselves
rarely catch a glimpse of the thieves.

01:51.528 --> 01:55.864
Many don't even know
they've been victimized until it's too late.

01:56.032 --> 02:00.744
In fact, police have yet to come up
with a single eyewitness.

02:00.912 --> 02:02.621
Only a few vague reports...

02:02.789 --> 02:06.708
...of young boys or teenagers
at the scenes have been filed.

02:06.876 --> 02:10.963
But whoever is behind these crimes,
one thing is certain.

02:11.131 --> 02:16.718
These are much more than just a series
of random isolated incidents.

02:20.056 --> 02:22.349
Come on. Hurry up.

02:31.985 --> 02:33.485
Mm.

02:33.653 --> 02:35.070
Good.

02:40.994 --> 02:42.703
Crimes without criminals?

02:42.871 --> 02:44.580
An invisible gang at work?

02:44.747 --> 02:46.248
Who are we gonna call?

02:46.416 --> 02:49.585
Unfortunately,
the police are the only ones available...

02:49.752 --> 02:54.339
...to combat what some are already dubbing
"the silent crime wave."

02:54.507 --> 02:57.092
But perhaps the most
disturbing silence...

02:57.260 --> 02:59.761
...is that coming from city hall.

02:59.929 --> 03:03.432
April O'Neil,
Channel 3 Eyewitness News.

03:04.142 --> 03:05.809
MAN:
You gotta stop working so hard, April.

03:05.977 --> 03:08.687
APRIL: What, and give up
all this glamour? Ha-ha-ha.

03:08.855 --> 03:11.773
- Good night.
MAN: Good night.

03:18.781 --> 03:20.073
[DOOR CLOSES]

03:20.325 --> 03:21.366
[RATS SQUEAKING]

03:22.785 --> 03:24.119
[GASPS]

03:26.247 --> 03:27.789
[EXHALES]

03:42.096 --> 03:43.805
[RATTLING]

03:48.061 --> 03:49.978
TEEN 1:
Bad timing.

03:50.480 --> 03:51.855
You're telling me.

03:52.023 --> 03:55.067
TEEN 2: Get her purse. Hey, get her purse.
APRIL: Get away from me!

03:55.235 --> 03:57.486
- What do you think... Help!
TEEN 3: Get herjewelry.

03:57.654 --> 03:59.488
- Hurry up.
- Get the money. I got her watch.

03:59.656 --> 04:00.989
[WHIRRING]

04:01.157 --> 04:02.908
[APRIL GROANS, CLANGING]

04:03.076 --> 04:04.159
[RUNNING FOOTSTEPS]

04:04.327 --> 04:06.328
[BLOWS LANDING, TEENS GRUNTING]

04:09.666 --> 04:11.583
TEEN 1:
Whoa.

04:12.001 --> 04:14.211
[SIREN WAILS]

04:15.088 --> 04:17.047
[POLICE RADIO CHATTER,
CAR DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

04:17.214 --> 04:18.257
[COUGHS]

04:18.423 --> 04:20.801
COP 1: What the hell's going on?
Thought I'd seen it all.

04:22.011 --> 04:23.345
COP 2:
Ready.

04:24.681 --> 04:27.391
All right. You tough guys.

04:27.558 --> 04:30.519
Roll over here. How did you
get yourself into this, huh, kid?

04:30.687 --> 04:32.521
- You all right, ma'am?
APRIL: Yeah, I'm fine.

04:32.689 --> 04:35.857
COP 1: Listen, rest right here
while we deal with these guys.

04:37.026 --> 04:38.527
[COP 1 TALKS INDISTINCTLY]

04:42.907 --> 04:45.158
COP 1: Ted, give John a hand.
COP 2: What you got there?

04:46.286 --> 04:47.536
MALE VOICE:
Oh, man.

04:48.413 --> 04:50.706
COP 1:
Come on, no fighting.

04:50.873 --> 04:52.874
- Untie me.
- Let's get them in the car.

04:53.042 --> 04:54.793
MALE VOICE:
Damn.

05:19.569 --> 05:20.610
[LAUGHTER]

05:20.778 --> 05:22.070
MALE VOICE 1:
Spectacular.

05:22.238 --> 05:25.449
MALE VOICE 2: We were awesome, bros.
MALE VOICE 3: Far out. Ow!

05:25.616 --> 05:26.992
Yes, dudes and dudettes...

05:27.160 --> 05:29.578
...major league butt-kicking
is back in town.

05:29.746 --> 05:30.746
MALE VOICES:
Oh, yeah.

05:36.252 --> 05:37.627
Awesome.

05:37.795 --> 05:40.005
Ha-ha-ha. Righteous.

05:40.173 --> 05:41.465
Bossa nova!

05:41.632 --> 05:43.467
- What?
- Huh?

05:43.634 --> 05:45.552
Bossa nova?

05:45.720 --> 05:47.763
- Chevy Nova?
- Oh.

05:47.930 --> 05:50.057
[GROANS]

05:50.308 --> 05:51.433
Excellent.

05:51.601 --> 05:54.144
- Yeah.
- All right.

05:54.312 --> 05:57.147
- Come on, let's move it. I'm starving.
- Ooh.

05:57.315 --> 06:00.567
Ooh. We're talking
major pizza attack here, dudes.

06:00.735 --> 06:02.778
DONATELLO:
Pizza. I need it.

06:02.945 --> 06:04.279
Oh, baby.

06:04.447 --> 06:05.864
Oh, man.

06:06.032 --> 06:07.699
LEONARDO:
All right.

06:07.867 --> 06:09.117
[TURTLES CHUCKLING]

06:09.285 --> 06:11.119
- Evening, bros.
- Whoo!

06:11.287 --> 06:13.121
- Give me three.
- You got it.

06:13.289 --> 06:16.291
[ALL CHUCKLING]

06:17.168 --> 06:20.379
We were great. I can't believe it.

06:21.756 --> 06:23.423
Damn!

06:26.386 --> 06:29.137
DONATELLO:
All right. Shh, shh.

06:29.305 --> 06:31.473
Ha-ha.

06:31.641 --> 06:34.851
We have had our first battle,
Master Splinter.

06:35.019 --> 06:37.270
They were many, but we kicked...

06:37.438 --> 06:38.855
[SPLINTER CLEARS THROAT]

06:39.023 --> 06:41.233
- We fought well.
- Mm-hm.

06:41.776 --> 06:44.236
SPLINTER: Were you seen?
- Mm-mm.

06:44.779 --> 06:48.448
In this you must never lapse.

06:48.616 --> 06:54.204
Even those who would be our allies
would not understand.

06:54.372 --> 06:57.457
Our domain is the shadow.

06:57.625 --> 06:59.835
Stray from it reluctantly.

07:00.002 --> 07:01.378
For when you do...

07:01.546 --> 07:06.007
...you must strike hard and fade away...

07:06.759 --> 07:09.302
...without a trace.

07:10.680 --> 07:12.013
I lost a sai.

07:12.181 --> 07:14.641
- Then it is gone.
- But I can get it back. I can.

07:14.809 --> 07:17.853
Raphael, let it go.

07:18.020 --> 07:19.396
[BOTH GRUNT]

07:19.564 --> 07:21.022
SPLINTER:
Hey.

07:22.567 --> 07:23.692
[GRUNTS]

07:24.277 --> 07:28.488
Your ninja skills are reaching their peak.

07:28.656 --> 07:35.203
Only one truly important lesson remains,
but must wait.

07:35.621 --> 07:40.041
I know it is hard for you
here underground.

07:40.209 --> 07:42.836
I want a large thick crust
with double cheese...

07:43.004 --> 07:44.379
...ham, pepperoni.

07:44.714 --> 07:48.383
Your teenage minds are broad, eager.

07:48.551 --> 07:53.346
But you must never stop practicing
the art of ninja...

07:53.514 --> 07:57.476
...the art of invisibility.

07:57.643 --> 07:59.060
MICHAELANGELO:
Oh, but no anchovies.

07:59.228 --> 08:01.229
And I mean no anchovies.

08:01.397 --> 08:05.025
You put anchovies on this thing
and you're in big trouble, okay?

08:05.193 --> 08:06.234
Michaelangelo!

08:06.402 --> 08:08.820
That'll do. And the clock's ticking, dude.

08:09.071 --> 08:11.823
[TURTLES CHUCKLING]

08:13.451 --> 08:15.869
You are still young...

08:16.037 --> 08:20.373
...but one day, I will be gone.

08:20.541 --> 08:23.877
Use my teachings wisely.

08:24.754 --> 08:27.797
I suggest we all meditate now...

08:27.965 --> 08:30.550
...on the events of this evening.

08:30.968 --> 08:32.969
[BREATHING DEEPLY]

08:36.097 --> 08:39.100
["TEQUILA" PLAYING]

08:40.102 --> 08:41.727
TURTLES:
Yeah.

08:42.605 --> 08:47.150
Yeah.

08:47.944 --> 08:50.195
BOTH:
Ninjitsu.

08:50.780 --> 08:52.364
Well, this is like meditating.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.869
Hey, Raph, where you going?

08:58.037 --> 09:00.205
Out to a movie.

09:01.290 --> 09:03.124
That okay with you?

09:03.292 --> 09:04.960
Yeah.

09:10.841 --> 09:13.301
Sock it to me, baby.

09:31.654 --> 09:34.489
- How you doing?
- Fine.

09:36.492 --> 09:37.826
DONATELLO:
Nice night.

09:38.619 --> 09:39.869
Mm-hm.

09:40.037 --> 09:42.372
Pizza dude's got 30 seconds.

09:42.540 --> 09:44.207
Mm-hm.

09:45.835 --> 09:49.921
Hey, Mikey, did you ever think
about what Splinter said tonight?

09:50.089 --> 09:52.632
I mean, about what it would be like...

09:52.800 --> 09:55.927
...you know, not having him?

09:56.137 --> 09:57.804
Hmm.

09:58.306 --> 10:02.267
- Time's up. Three bucks off.
- Mm.

10:06.939 --> 10:08.773
Okay.

10:08.941 --> 10:10.275
[GRUNTS]

10:12.194 --> 10:13.194
[SIGHS]

10:13.362 --> 10:14.404
[WHISTLES]

10:14.572 --> 10:18.950
Now, 122, 122 and an eighth?

10:19.535 --> 10:23.872
122 and an eighth. Terrific.

10:24.040 --> 10:26.666
Where the heck is 122 and an eighth?

10:26.834 --> 10:29.377
MICHAELANGELO:
You're standing on it, dude.

10:30.129 --> 10:32.505
Just slip it down here.

10:38.763 --> 10:39.888
[MAN GRUNTS]

10:40.056 --> 10:41.222
MICHAELANGELO:
Give me that.

10:42.600 --> 10:46.186
Hey, this is a 10. The tab's 13.

10:46.354 --> 10:48.063
MICHAELANGELO:
You're two minutes late, dude.

10:48.230 --> 10:50.690
Oh, come on. I couldn't find the place.

10:50.858 --> 10:53.443
MICHAELANGELO:
Wise man say, "Forgiveness is divine...

10:53.611 --> 10:57.197
...but never pay full price for late pizza."

10:57.740 --> 11:01.701
I gotta get a new route.
And I thought I delivered everywhere.

11:01.869 --> 11:05.205
MICHAELANGELO:
Yes, friends, the new Turbo Ginsu.

11:05.373 --> 11:07.082
It dices, it slices...

11:07.249 --> 11:10.752
...and yet makes French fries
in three different...

11:10.920 --> 11:12.295
Whoops!

11:12.463 --> 11:13.922
Mm. Kids.

11:14.090 --> 11:16.132
[HUMS]

11:16.425 --> 11:18.009
Hmm.

11:18.719 --> 11:19.928
[CHUCKLING]

11:20.096 --> 11:22.806
- There's a joke on the...
- I know.

11:26.519 --> 11:27.769
Ugh.

11:27.937 --> 11:30.397
Where do they come up with this stuff?

11:30.564 --> 11:32.565
[PEOPLE CHATTERING, CHUCKLING]

11:38.864 --> 11:41.282
MAN 1: Hey.
MAN 2: Hey.

11:41.450 --> 11:43.368
MAN 1: Come back here.
WOMAN: Somebody stop them.

11:44.787 --> 11:46.037
[GRUNTS]

11:46.997 --> 11:48.248
- Where's the...?
- What?

11:48.416 --> 11:49.582
- Huh?
- Huh.

11:50.793 --> 11:52.460
Mm-mm.

11:53.587 --> 11:54.796
BOTH:
Whoa.

11:55.297 --> 11:58.383
[THIEVES GRUNT]

12:01.554 --> 12:03.096
What the hell was that?

12:03.264 --> 12:04.431
I don't know.

12:05.141 --> 12:08.643
Now, that was a crime,
you purse-grabbing pukes...

12:08.811 --> 12:10.895
...and this is the penalty.

12:12.481 --> 12:15.817
Two minutes for slashing,
two minutes for hooking...

12:15.985 --> 12:18.528
...and let's not forget
my personal favorite...

12:18.696 --> 12:21.239
...two minutes for high-sticking.
THIEF 1: Aah!

12:22.450 --> 12:25.994
How about a five-minute game misconduct
for roughing, pal?

12:26.162 --> 12:29.247
Hey, Bogie,
now, who died and made you referee?

12:29.415 --> 12:31.207
You did yourjob, now let me do mine.

12:31.375 --> 12:32.917
These JV lowlifes need a lesson.

12:33.210 --> 12:34.669
Not like that they don't.

12:34.837 --> 12:36.755
Not from you.

12:40.009 --> 12:43.845
Well, it looks like you're the one
who needs to be taught a lesson, pal.

12:44.096 --> 12:47.849
Class is Pain 101.
Your instructor is Casey Jones.

12:48.184 --> 12:50.685
Look, I don't wanna fight you.

12:50.853 --> 12:52.520
Well, tough rocks, pal.

12:52.688 --> 12:55.356
[GRUNTING]

12:55.524 --> 12:57.734
A Jose Canseco bat?

12:57.902 --> 13:01.154
- Tell me you didn't pay money for this.
- Ooh.

13:01.322 --> 13:02.864
That's it.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.200
Was a two-for-one sale, pal.

13:05.534 --> 13:06.534
[GRUNTS]

13:08.120 --> 13:10.622
- Hey, what are you, some sort of punker?
- Huh?

13:11.624 --> 13:13.792
God, I hate punkers.

13:14.251 --> 13:16.753
Especially bald ones
with green makeup...

13:16.921 --> 13:19.714
...who wear masks over ugly faces.
- That's it.

13:19.882 --> 13:21.883
- Ooh.
- New batter.

13:22.051 --> 13:23.676
CASEY:
Strike one.

13:23.969 --> 13:25.553
Whoa. Whiffer.

13:28.349 --> 13:30.391
- Ooh. Uhn!
- Home run.

13:31.977 --> 13:33.561
Raphael wins.

13:33.729 --> 13:36.231
One-nothing!

13:36.398 --> 13:38.858
[GRUNTING]

13:40.569 --> 13:41.694
Well?

13:41.862 --> 13:43.696
New game, roundhead.

13:46.200 --> 13:48.493
- Cricket.
- Cricket?

13:48.661 --> 13:50.537
Nobody understands cricket.

13:50.704 --> 13:53.414
You gotta know what a crumpet is
to understand cricket.

13:53.916 --> 13:55.416
I'll teach you.

13:57.753 --> 14:01.256
- Ooh...
- See? Six runs.

14:01.715 --> 14:03.716
[GROANING, GRUNTING]

14:07.596 --> 14:09.430
CASEY:
So long, freak. I got work to do.

14:09.598 --> 14:11.599
Freak?

14:12.351 --> 14:14.227
Freak!

14:18.774 --> 14:19.858
[GRUNTS]

14:20.818 --> 14:22.026
What the heck was that?

14:22.194 --> 14:25.780
Looked like sort of a big turtle
in a trench coat.

14:26.115 --> 14:28.241
You're going to LaGuardia, right?

14:28.409 --> 14:29.659
RAPHAEL:
Come back here.

14:29.827 --> 14:31.077
I'm not finished with you.

14:32.121 --> 14:34.497
Damn!

14:39.003 --> 14:41.004
[DOOR CREAKS]

14:46.552 --> 14:48.303
SPLINTER:
Raphael.

14:48.470 --> 14:50.138
Come sit by me.

14:50.598 --> 14:52.056
Couldrt this wait till morning?

14:52.224 --> 14:55.059
You will listen now.

15:04.194 --> 15:09.324
My master Yoshi's first rule...

15:10.409 --> 15:12.994
...was possess the right thinking.

15:13.162 --> 15:16.331
Only then can one receive...

15:16.498 --> 15:21.669
...the gifts of strength,
knowledge and peace.

15:25.174 --> 15:29.510
I have tried to channel your anger,
Raphael...

15:29.678 --> 15:32.096
...but more remains.

15:32.264 --> 15:35.516
Anger clouds the mind.

15:35.684 --> 15:41.022
Turned inward,
it is an unconquerable enemy.

15:41.273 --> 15:45.360
You are unique among your brothers...

15:45.527 --> 15:50.531
...for you choose
to face this enemy alone.

15:50.699 --> 15:56.162
But as you face it, do not forget them.

15:56.330 --> 15:59.666
And do not forget me.

15:59.833 --> 16:01.292
[RAPHAEL CRYING SOFTLY]

16:01.460 --> 16:07.215
I am here, my son.

16:08.217 --> 16:11.219
CHARLES: Come on, April, you could've
called me last night, you know?

16:11.387 --> 16:15.390
Call it a quirk, but I like to know when one
of my best reporters has been mugged.

16:15.557 --> 16:17.392
I wasrt mugged, Charles.

16:17.559 --> 16:21.938
Besides, I knew you'd just worry and then
rush over here like you did this morning.

16:22.106 --> 16:24.107
From now on,
security is gonna escort you...

16:24.274 --> 16:27.235
...to that Stone-Age van of yours
every night.

16:27.403 --> 16:29.445
- Yes, sir.
CHARLES: I'm not kidding, April.

16:29.613 --> 16:32.407
APRIL:
Ugh. Hey, Danny, how's school going?

16:32.574 --> 16:34.409
- Fine.
- Oh, wonderful.

16:35.285 --> 16:38.121
So wonderful I have to drive him there
every morning now...

16:38.288 --> 16:40.456
...just to make sure he goes.

16:41.250 --> 16:42.625
See?

16:42.793 --> 16:45.003
That's what he does
when he wants to ignore me.

16:45.170 --> 16:46.587
Sticks his head in those things.

16:46.755 --> 16:48.631
[MUSIC PLAYING OVER HEADPHONES,
CHARLES SIGHS]

16:48.799 --> 16:51.592
I wonder where the hell
he got those things, anyway.

16:51.760 --> 16:54.095
APRIL:
Charles, give the kid a break.

16:54.263 --> 16:55.555
[CHARLES SIGHS]

16:56.390 --> 16:58.599
Just what is going on out there, April?

16:59.810 --> 17:01.853
I've never seen anything like this before.

17:02.604 --> 17:04.105
Like the city's falling apart.

17:04.272 --> 17:07.191
It's getting so you can't step outside
in the daytime anymore.

17:07.776 --> 17:09.234
APRIL:
Well, I'll tell you one thing.

17:09.403 --> 17:11.738
After everything I've heard
out of Little Tokyo...

17:11.905 --> 17:14.699
...Sterns is gonna have some answering
to do this afternoon.

17:14.867 --> 17:17.993
Look. Just take it easy, okay?

17:18.162 --> 17:20.621
He's already got the mayor
breathing down my neck.

17:20.955 --> 17:23.750
We are presently executing a plan
of redeployment...

17:23.916 --> 17:25.667
...that will minimize response time...

17:25.836 --> 17:29.255
...while maximizing coordination
between patrol units...

17:29.423 --> 17:32.800
...in a decentralized networking scheme.

17:34.428 --> 17:38.014
Huh. I'm not sure I understood all that,
Chief Sterns.

17:38.182 --> 17:39.599
Would you mind repeating it...

17:39.767 --> 17:42.351
...in English, perhaps?

17:43.020 --> 17:47.482
What that means, Miss O'Neil,
is that we have everything well in hand.

17:47.649 --> 17:50.193
- You know why crimes have been escalating.
- Guys, look.

17:50.360 --> 17:53.738
- That's her.
- No, I didn't say that either. Miss O'Neil...

17:53.906 --> 17:58.117
...if you would stick to asking questions,
there would be a lot...

17:58.285 --> 18:01.662
- Mmm. I'm in love.
- What do you know about an organization...

18:01.830 --> 18:04.290
...known as The Foot Clan?

18:04.541 --> 18:07.335
There is no evidence
to link such a name to these incidents.

18:07.503 --> 18:11.255
Are you denying that such an organization
known as The Foot exists?

18:11.673 --> 18:13.257
I'm not denying anything.

18:13.425 --> 18:16.594
Again, you're putting words
into my mouth.

18:16.762 --> 18:19.722
- Find her.
- It often seems that somebody ought to.

18:19.890 --> 18:22.266
- Silence her.
- Miss O'Neil...

18:22.434 --> 18:25.645
- She's great.
- An understatement as usual.

18:25.813 --> 18:27.814
- You're telling me.
- The girl is a fox.

18:27.981 --> 18:31.275
MAN [ON TV]: Look at the local weather
for this vicinity as it stands at this hour.

18:31.443 --> 18:34.862
STERNS:
O'Neil, get in here.

18:36.031 --> 18:37.782
Time me.

18:44.373 --> 18:48.167
Just what is it you hoped to accomplish
out there besides busting my chops?

18:49.795 --> 18:52.880
I think you know just as much as I do
about this Foot Clan...

18:53.048 --> 18:55.466
...and I don't think
you're doing anything about it.

18:55.634 --> 18:57.301
You expect me to waste manpower...

18:57.678 --> 18:59.679
...because a few immigrants
are reminded...

18:59.847 --> 19:02.807
...of something that supposedly happened
years ago in Japan?

19:02.975 --> 19:04.350
Have you got something else?

19:05.644 --> 19:08.521
Are you trying to tell me
how to do my job?

19:10.649 --> 19:13.526
One-oh-seven, a new record.

19:33.964 --> 19:36.215
Oh, great.

19:36.383 --> 19:37.717
Just great.

19:41.346 --> 19:42.805
[SIGHS]

19:46.268 --> 19:48.603
[WHOOSHING, APRIL GASPS]

19:48.770 --> 19:51.189
[IN ASIAN ACCENT]
We've been waiting for you, Miss O'Neil.

19:51.940 --> 19:53.274
What?

19:53.442 --> 19:56.152
Am I behind
on my Sony payments again? Ha-ha-ha.

19:56.320 --> 20:00.323
Your mouth may yet bring you
much trouble, Miss O'Neil.

20:00.532 --> 20:01.908
I deliver a message.

20:05.078 --> 20:07.413
- Hah!
- Shut it.

20:12.127 --> 20:14.128
All right. That's it.

20:14.296 --> 20:16.297
[GRUNTING]

20:23.180 --> 20:25.473
[RAPHAEL SCREAMS]

20:25.807 --> 20:27.266
[GRUNTING]

20:48.413 --> 20:50.414
[PANTING]

21:01.009 --> 21:03.094
[RUMBLING IN DISTANCE]

21:15.941 --> 21:17.650
Are you crazy?

21:18.777 --> 21:21.404
Yeah, Leo, I'm crazy. Okay?

21:21.571 --> 21:23.072
A loony. Okay?

21:23.240 --> 21:24.282
DONATELLO:
Why?

21:24.449 --> 21:27.201
Why? Why? Oh, I don't know.

21:27.369 --> 21:28.911
Because I wanted to redecorate.

21:29.079 --> 21:32.164
You know, a couple of throw pillows,
a TV news reporter.

21:32.332 --> 21:33.833
- What do you think?
- Ahem.

21:34.001 --> 21:36.168
SPLINTER:
Raphael, what are you doing?

21:36.336 --> 21:39.130
She got jumped in the subway.
I had to bring her here.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.215
It's the newslady.

21:42.175 --> 21:43.342
Can we keep her?

21:44.845 --> 21:48.139
- Bring water, cold washcloth, pillow.
- Far out.

21:59.526 --> 22:01.110
APRIL:
Oh...

22:03.822 --> 22:06.574
[SCREAMING]

22:06.992 --> 22:08.743
Hi.

22:09.328 --> 22:12.913
[ALL SCREAMING]

22:13.540 --> 22:15.916
Oh, my God. Oh, my God. I'm dead.

22:16.084 --> 22:17.877
- I'm dead, aren't I?
- It's okay.

22:18.045 --> 22:20.087
No, I'm dreaming. I must be dreaming.

22:20.255 --> 22:23.841
Okay. Now, those guys
in the black pajamas, they jumped me.

22:24.009 --> 22:25.384
And that rat...

22:25.552 --> 22:28.262
...I saw you in the parking lot.
That explains you.

22:28.513 --> 22:31.766
- And you guys... Um...
- Hmm?

22:31.933 --> 22:33.184
[WHIMPERING]

22:33.352 --> 22:35.853
...I have no idea where you came from.

22:36.021 --> 22:39.940
If you will please just sit down
and calm yourself.

22:40.275 --> 22:42.234
I will tell you where we came from.

22:42.402 --> 22:43.486
It talks.

22:43.653 --> 22:46.781
It is really quite simple, Miss O'Neil.

22:47.282 --> 22:49.867
And he knows my name.

22:50.035 --> 22:51.827
Perfect.

22:51.995 --> 22:54.080
Fifteen years ago...

22:54.247 --> 22:57.124
Why don't I ever dream
of Harrison Ford?

22:57.292 --> 22:58.501
[SIGHS]

23:00.295 --> 23:04.757
For 15 years now, we have lived here.

23:04.925 --> 23:11.722
Before that time,
I was a pet of my master Yoshi...

23:11.890 --> 23:15.393
...mimicking his movements
from my cage...

23:15.560 --> 23:19.313
...and learning the secret art of ninja.

23:20.399 --> 23:24.276
When we were forced
to come to New York...

23:24.444 --> 23:29.782
...I found myself for the first time
without a home...

23:29.950 --> 23:34.912
...wandering the sewers,
scavenging for whatever I could find.

23:35.080 --> 23:37.123
And then, one day...

23:37.290 --> 23:40.000
...I came upon a shattered glass jar...

23:40.168 --> 23:42.586
...and four baby turtles.

23:42.754 --> 23:44.296
- That was us. Heh-heh.
- Shut up.

23:44.464 --> 23:47.466
- Oh, no.
- Oh.

23:47.676 --> 23:52.847
The little ones were crawling
into a strange glowing ooze...

23:53.014 --> 23:56.517
...from a broken canister nearby.

23:57.102 --> 24:00.312
I gathered them up in an old coffee can...

24:00.480 --> 24:04.692
...and when I awoke the next morning,
I received a shock...

24:04.860 --> 24:08.070
...for they had doubled in size.

24:08.238 --> 24:12.533
I too was growing,
particularly in intellect...

24:12.701 --> 24:16.454
...and I was amazed
at how intelligent they seemed.

24:16.621 --> 24:21.167
But nothing could have prepared me
for what happened next.

24:21.334 --> 24:23.169
One of them spoke.

24:23.336 --> 24:25.796
Pizza.

24:25.964 --> 24:27.673
More words followed...

24:28.008 --> 24:30.259
...and I began their training...

24:30.427 --> 24:33.804
...teaching them all that I had learned
from my master.

24:34.181 --> 24:35.890
Radical. Radical. Radical.

24:36.057 --> 24:39.560
And soon I gave them all names...

24:39.978 --> 24:41.854
...Leonardo...

24:42.022 --> 24:44.190
...Michaelangelo...
- That's me.

24:44.357 --> 24:45.858
...Donatello...

24:46.026 --> 24:48.569
...and Raphael.

24:52.866 --> 24:55.868
I'm not dreaming, am I?

24:56.036 --> 24:58.370
No, I'm afraid not.

25:03.084 --> 25:06.879
APRIL: Ew. Are you guys sure
you know where you're going?

25:07.047 --> 25:08.255
MICHAELANGELO:
11th and Bleecker?

25:08.423 --> 25:09.465
[SNIFFS]

25:09.633 --> 25:11.425
Nope. This is only 9th Street. Ha.

25:11.593 --> 25:12.635
- Get it?
APRIL: Yuck.

25:12.802 --> 25:14.553
Okay.

25:27.359 --> 25:29.151
Ah...

25:29.319 --> 25:31.862
I'd like to invite you all in...

25:32.030 --> 25:35.950
...but I really don't have anything to offer
you guys except for frozen pizza.

25:36.576 --> 25:38.452
Let's go for it.

25:39.788 --> 25:41.121
You said the magic word.

25:41.623 --> 25:44.708
- You guys eat pizza?
BOTH: Doesrt everybody?

25:44.876 --> 25:46.752
Yeah, well...

25:47.295 --> 25:48.796
...all right.

25:49.464 --> 25:51.090
Hey, did she say pizza?

25:51.258 --> 25:53.133
- So you live in an antique store?
- Yep.

25:53.301 --> 25:54.426
Pizza.

25:54.594 --> 25:56.512
Well, above, actually.

25:57.597 --> 25:59.765
What do you guys like on your pizza?

25:59.933 --> 26:01.475
Just the regular stuff.

26:01.643 --> 26:03.227
Flies, stink bugs.

26:03.395 --> 26:04.937
[MANHOLE COVER SLIDES]

26:05.105 --> 26:06.772
It was a joke. Ha-ha.

26:07.065 --> 26:09.066
[ALL LAUGH]

26:10.527 --> 26:13.571
[GRUNTING LIKE A BOXER]

26:13.738 --> 26:16.156
[IMITATING ROCKY]
Yeah, well, maybe I'll fight Apollo...

26:16.324 --> 26:17.992
...maybe I won't, you know?

26:18.159 --> 26:19.326
What do you think?

26:19.494 --> 26:21.579
- Adrian!
- Ha-ha-ha.

26:21.746 --> 26:23.163
Hey, I got another one.

26:23.790 --> 26:26.917
APRIL: This is totally cool.
- Oh, no, not Cagney.

26:28.044 --> 26:30.504
[IMITATING JAMES CAGNEY]
Mmm. You dirty rat.

26:30.672 --> 26:32.172
You killed my brother.

26:32.340 --> 26:34.383
You dirty rat. Mmm.

26:35.260 --> 26:37.011
Whoo-hoo. Ha-ha-ha.

26:37.178 --> 26:39.847
That must be Splinter's favorite. Ha-ha-ha.

26:40.015 --> 26:43.475
TURTLES:
Huh?

26:44.853 --> 26:47.438
- It was a joke.
- Hmm?

26:48.773 --> 26:50.774
[ALL LAUGHING]

26:55.447 --> 26:59.116
And speaking of which,
we better get going.

26:59.284 --> 27:00.701
He worries.

27:00.994 --> 27:05.080
Oh. Well, I don't know what to say.

27:05.248 --> 27:07.875
- Will I ever see you guys again?
- Indubitably.

27:08.043 --> 27:10.711
That depends
on how fast you stock your pizza.

27:10.879 --> 27:13.172
- Deal.
- See you around.

27:13.340 --> 27:15.758
- Bye.
- Later.

27:21.389 --> 27:24.058
DONATELLO:
Ha-ha. No doubt about it. She loved us.

27:24.225 --> 27:25.726
MICHAELANGELO:
It was the impressions, dudes.

27:25.894 --> 27:27.394
- You wish.
- Hold it.

27:43.036 --> 27:44.912
Splinter.

27:54.089 --> 27:56.090
[CRYING]

27:56.883 --> 28:00.427
[SCREAMS]

28:13.650 --> 28:14.817
APRIL:
What's wrong?

28:14.984 --> 28:16.276
Splinter.

28:16.444 --> 28:18.570
[SOBS SOFTLY]

28:25.495 --> 28:29.248
STERNS:
555-5215.

28:34.295 --> 28:35.295
[LINE RINGS]

28:35.463 --> 28:37.047
CHARLES [OVER PHONE]: Hello.
- Hello.

28:37.215 --> 28:38.382
Charles Pennington?

28:38.550 --> 28:40.008
Yeah. Who's this?

28:40.176 --> 28:42.761
You got a son named Danny, Charles?

28:48.643 --> 28:50.644
[TURTLES SNORING]

28:54.941 --> 28:57.818
[TURTLES YAWN]

28:58.236 --> 28:59.278
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

28:59.446 --> 29:00.487
[TURTLES GASP]

29:00.655 --> 29:01.697
Who is it?

29:01.865 --> 29:04.950
CHARLES: It's me, Charles.
- It's my boss.

29:05.118 --> 29:06.160
[WHOOSHING]

29:06.327 --> 29:07.661
Can you guys...

29:08.913 --> 29:10.456
...hide?

29:15.462 --> 29:16.795
Charles, what's up?

29:16.963 --> 29:18.130
April...

29:18.298 --> 29:19.798
...listen.

29:21.176 --> 29:25.804
I've... You have been working awful hard
on this story lately.

29:25.972 --> 29:29.892
Why don't you take it easy for a while?
Just... Just...

29:30.643 --> 29:33.020
Just let somebody else handle it.

29:34.522 --> 29:36.857
Just for a little while, you know?

29:37.025 --> 29:39.735
Charles, what are you talking about?
It's my story. No way.

29:39.903 --> 29:41.487
CHARLES:
Look at you. You're exhausted.

29:41.654 --> 29:42.863
APRIL:
I just had a rough night.

29:43.031 --> 29:45.824
CHARLES: Let somebody else help you
cover city hall.

29:45.992 --> 29:47.701
APRIL:
Charles, that's ridiculous.

29:47.869 --> 29:49.369
What's with you today?

29:49.662 --> 29:51.914
Nothing's with me today.

29:52.081 --> 29:54.291
I just thought you might like a little help.

29:54.459 --> 29:55.709
Well, I don't.

29:56.211 --> 29:59.671
- Hand me a towel, will you?
CHARLES: Where do you keep the towels?

29:59.839 --> 30:03.091
- Charles, no.
- What's wrong?

30:03.259 --> 30:06.929
I just... I just don't want you to see
my unsightly bathtub ring. Okay?

30:07.096 --> 30:09.348
Just out, out, out.

30:09.516 --> 30:11.141
I have to get ready for work.

30:11.309 --> 30:13.310
Are you sure you won't reconsider
some help?

30:13.478 --> 30:15.979
Hey, Danny,
will you tell your father to relax?

30:16.147 --> 30:17.856
I wish.

30:19.859 --> 30:23.028
Just don't push any buttons today.
Okay?

30:26.115 --> 30:28.826
- That was close. Whoa!
- Hah!

30:28.993 --> 30:32.037
Time to switch to decaf, April.

30:32.539 --> 30:34.373
I don't get it, Danny.

30:34.541 --> 30:37.918
I make enough money to provide
for both of us and you're stealing.

30:38.086 --> 30:39.127
Why?

30:39.295 --> 30:41.588
- I don't know.
- You don't know?

30:42.006 --> 30:44.216
What were you doing
with a car stereo anyway?

30:44.384 --> 30:45.509
Or don't you know?

30:45.677 --> 30:47.427
- Sorry.
- Sorry?

30:47.595 --> 30:50.347
Not as sorry as you're gonna be
after school.

30:52.141 --> 30:53.600
Danny, damn it.

30:53.768 --> 30:55.519
Danny, come back here.

30:55.687 --> 30:57.688
[HORNS HONKING]

31:01.526 --> 31:03.527
[LOUD MUSIC PLAYING]

31:07.073 --> 31:09.074
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

31:30.096 --> 31:31.680
BOY 1:
How are you doing?

31:36.477 --> 31:39.313
Check it out, man.
Anything you guys want, we got it.

31:39.480 --> 31:41.982
Anything you want to do...

31:42.150 --> 31:44.693
...do it. Know what I'm saying?
Anything.

31:44.861 --> 31:47.321
You got any cigarettes?

31:48.781 --> 31:51.283
Regular or menthol?

31:58.291 --> 31:59.791
BOY 2:
Read them and weep, boys.

31:59.959 --> 32:03.253
- Full house.
- Oh, no.

32:07.133 --> 32:08.967
Mmp! Mm-hm.

32:11.054 --> 32:13.639
Go. Play.

32:16.684 --> 32:17.768
BOY 3:
All right.

32:20.271 --> 32:21.855
- Hah!
- Oh!

32:22.023 --> 32:24.983
- Hah! Hah!
- Aah! Ooh!

32:25.151 --> 32:26.193
BOY 4:
How's this look?

32:26.861 --> 32:30.364
- Hah! Hah! Hah!
- Ooh.

32:30.531 --> 32:32.866
You. Hm!

32:35.703 --> 32:37.162
Mm.

32:43.086 --> 32:45.087
[GRUNTING]

32:48.466 --> 32:49.883
Good.

32:51.678 --> 32:54.221
[GRUNTING]

32:56.891 --> 33:00.519
Never lower your eyes to an enemy.

33:00.687 --> 33:02.854
Yes, Master Tatsu.

33:06.234 --> 33:07.943
[GONG SOUNDS]

33:08.945 --> 33:10.404
MAN:
All right.

33:10.905 --> 33:12.823
[CHATTERING]

33:13.408 --> 33:15.200
BOY:
Yeah. I am.

34:17.263 --> 34:19.473
Master Shredder.

34:35.822 --> 34:37.449
[GRUNTS]

35:00.890 --> 35:06.144
SHREDDER: Money cannot buy the honor
which you have earned tonight.

35:10.942 --> 35:14.361
You make us all proud.

35:18.199 --> 35:22.369
Only effort, discipline, loyalty...

35:22.537 --> 35:25.789
...earn the right to wear the dragon dogi.

35:26.165 --> 35:31.336
You are here
because the outside world rejects you.

35:31.504 --> 35:33.338
This is your family.

35:34.132 --> 35:37.134
I am your father.

35:37.301 --> 35:44.307
I want you all to become full members
of The Foot.

35:44.600 --> 35:47.185
There is a new enemy...

35:47.353 --> 35:52.107
...freaks of nature
who interfere with our business.

35:52.275 --> 35:56.403
You are my eyes and ears. Find them.

35:56.571 --> 36:00.615
Together we will punish these...

36:00.908 --> 36:03.076
...creatures.

36:03.411 --> 36:05.787
These...

36:06.581 --> 36:08.039
...turtles.

36:08.958 --> 36:10.625
BOY:
Master.

36:22.180 --> 36:24.139
This is beginning to sound
less and less...

36:24.307 --> 36:27.017
...like your common,
garden-variety subway mugging.

36:27.185 --> 36:29.769
- Exactly, June.
- Boy, she's a good reporter.

36:29.937 --> 36:34.274
- She's a babe.
- Organization known as The Foot.

36:34.442 --> 36:35.859
I'm sorry, The Foot?

36:36.027 --> 36:39.446
APRIL: Yeah, I know it sounds like
a funky club for podiatrists...

36:39.614 --> 36:43.158
...but I've been speaking with Japanese-
Americans in the past few days...

36:43.326 --> 36:45.785
...who say that our crime wave
is reminiscent...

36:45.953 --> 36:48.371
...of a secret band of ninja thieves...

36:48.539 --> 36:50.415
...who once operated in Japan.

36:50.583 --> 36:52.417
Are the police looking into this?

36:52.585 --> 36:54.628
I've included everything
in my statement...

36:54.795 --> 36:57.130
...but I doubt very much
that Chief Sterns...

36:57.298 --> 37:00.133
...is taking this possible connection
seriously.

37:00.718 --> 37:04.638
- I see. Well, perhaps if any of our viewers...
- Oh, God.

37:04.805 --> 37:06.640
WOMAN:
Mr. Pennington, Chief Sterns' office.

37:06.807 --> 37:09.017
- Contact local police
or get in touch with us...

37:09.185 --> 37:11.478
STERNS [OVER PHONE]:
Pennington, I thought we had a deal!

37:11.771 --> 37:14.648
You still haven't told us
how you got away from your attacker.

37:14.815 --> 37:17.067
It's really quite incredible.

37:17.610 --> 37:20.946
Some citizens of New York
actually came to my rescue.

37:21.113 --> 37:24.658
Who says everyone in the Big Apple
looks the other way?

37:24.825 --> 37:27.285
Seriously,
I would like to take this opportunity...

37:27.453 --> 37:31.498
...to thank one of those individuals
in particular.

37:31.666 --> 37:34.834
And if he's watching, thanks, Raphael.

37:35.002 --> 37:36.503
[ALL CHUCKLING]

37:36.671 --> 37:38.171
Studly.

37:38.339 --> 37:39.589
Hey, look. Nyak-nyak.

37:39.757 --> 37:41.383
I think he's blushing. Heh.

37:41.550 --> 37:42.842
I am not.

37:43.302 --> 37:44.928
I think he's actually turning red.

37:45.096 --> 37:47.180
[GRUNTS]

37:47.765 --> 37:50.100
- Uh, hmm. Maybe not.
- Mm-hm.

37:51.727 --> 37:53.353
So, what do we do now?

37:53.521 --> 37:56.898
- What do you mean, what do we do now?
- Splinter's out there somewhere.

37:57.066 --> 37:59.025
I know Splinter's out there.

37:59.193 --> 38:00.568
- Fight?
- Fight.

38:00.736 --> 38:01.778
- Kitchen?
- Kitchen.

38:01.946 --> 38:04.614
- Yeah.
- So, what are we gonna do about it?

38:04.782 --> 38:06.157
LEONARDO:
What can we do about it?

38:06.325 --> 38:08.493
April's our only link to these guys.

38:08.661 --> 38:11.204
We have to wait
until she comes up with something.

38:11.372 --> 38:17.002
Oh, so that's the plan
from our great leader, huh?

38:17.169 --> 38:18.837
Just sit here on our butts.

38:19.005 --> 38:21.881
I never said I was your great leader.

38:22.049 --> 38:23.800
Well, you sure act like it sometimes.

38:23.968 --> 38:27.220
Yeah? Well, you act like a jerk sometimes,
you know that?

38:27.388 --> 38:30.223
And this attitude of yours
isn't helping anything.

38:30.391 --> 38:33.393
Well, maybe I'll just take my attitude
and leave!

38:33.561 --> 38:35.186
- Why don't you?
- I will.

38:35.354 --> 38:36.521
- Good.
- Great.

38:36.689 --> 38:39.065
Go ahead. We don't need you.

38:39.400 --> 38:41.276
[CHEWING NOISILY]

38:41.444 --> 38:43.236
Pork rind?

38:43.404 --> 38:45.196
Pork rind.

38:46.073 --> 38:47.699
Damn!

38:49.952 --> 38:51.244
Hah!

38:52.121 --> 38:53.747
Ha-ah!

38:55.082 --> 38:57.083
[TUNING]

39:27.615 --> 39:28.656
[GUNSHOT OVER TV]

39:28.824 --> 39:30.033
Go.

39:30.201 --> 39:31.534
Move it, will you?

39:31.702 --> 39:33.453
You're letting him blow right by you.

39:33.621 --> 39:35.497
- Can you believe this guy?
- Hmm?

39:35.664 --> 39:37.290
Come on. Don't just...

39:37.458 --> 39:40.293
Ninja-kick the damn rabbit.
Do something.

39:40.461 --> 39:41.920
Hey.

39:42.129 --> 39:45.465
- April, hey, you were great.
- Thanks, Mikey.

39:45.633 --> 39:48.510
Ho... She called me Mikey.

39:48.677 --> 39:51.638
[CHUCKLING]

39:53.432 --> 39:55.225
Hear anything yet?

39:55.393 --> 39:57.102
Not yet.

39:57.645 --> 39:59.813
They're gonna repeat the interview
at 5 and 6.

39:59.980 --> 40:03.566
And we're gonna have to wait and see
if it helps generate any new information.

40:03.734 --> 40:05.318
Mmm.

40:05.486 --> 40:07.779
Hey, I told them to call me here
immediately...

40:07.947 --> 40:09.989
...if anyone calls the station.

40:10.157 --> 40:11.574
Thanks, April.

40:11.742 --> 40:14.661
We really appreciate,
you know, everything.

40:14.829 --> 40:15.995
Yeah.

40:16.163 --> 40:18.665
Hey, forget it.

40:20.000 --> 40:21.418
Where's Raphael?

40:24.922 --> 40:27.173
[RAPHAEL PANTING, GRUNTING]

40:27.675 --> 40:31.678
Well, I was gonna give you guys
a tour of the store.

40:31.846 --> 40:35.098
- Shall we go get him?
BOTH: No.

40:35.266 --> 40:37.934
- He just needs to blow off some steam.
- Yeah.

40:38.394 --> 40:42.689
You guys must be studying
the abridged book of ninja fighting.

40:43.232 --> 40:45.233
[GRUNTING]

40:50.322 --> 40:52.740
Come on, come here. Come here.

40:57.663 --> 40:59.038
I mean, come on.

40:59.206 --> 41:02.041
How do you guys expect to beat me?

41:04.462 --> 41:07.672
Good answer.

41:08.174 --> 41:11.885
APRIL: I only keep it open part-time,
mostly for my dad.

41:12.052 --> 41:14.053
Heh. He loved junk.

41:14.221 --> 41:16.973
I don't know.
It's dumb to lose money on a business...

41:17.141 --> 41:19.350
...just because you miss your father.

41:19.518 --> 41:21.436
LEONARDO:
No, it isn't.

41:23.731 --> 41:24.731
Ready?

41:26.734 --> 41:28.151
[GRUNTING]

41:32.740 --> 41:36.409
- This place has everything.
- Yup, just about.

41:37.077 --> 41:38.620
Shh.

41:39.747 --> 41:41.664
Eeeee.

41:42.666 --> 41:44.626
Aah!

41:44.835 --> 41:46.836
[GRUNTING]

41:49.006 --> 41:51.007
APRIL:
Hasrt Raph been gone a long time?

41:51.175 --> 41:53.593
No. He does it all the time. He likes it.

41:53.886 --> 41:55.512
[GROANING]

41:55.721 --> 41:57.180
Are you sure?

41:57.348 --> 42:01.100
Don't worry.
He'll probably be back any minute.

42:02.436 --> 42:03.728
APRIL:
Raph!

42:04.313 --> 42:05.355
Is he...?

42:05.523 --> 42:07.232
- No, he's alive. Barely.
APRIL: Oh, God.

42:10.778 --> 42:12.028
[YELLING]

42:17.451 --> 42:19.786
- Hey, what the...?
MICHAELANGELO: Whoa.

42:19.954 --> 42:22.372
And I thought insurance salesmen
were pushy.

42:22.998 --> 42:25.959
[PANTING]

42:26.460 --> 42:29.879
Ohh. A fellow chucker, eh?

42:31.924 --> 42:33.383
What?

42:33.551 --> 42:38.096
Oh-woh-oh. Oh-oh.
Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh. Wah!

42:38.556 --> 42:39.597
[ALL MURMURING]

42:39.765 --> 42:41.766
[GRUNTING]

42:44.395 --> 42:46.396
[HUMMING, GRUNTING]

42:49.650 --> 42:51.401
Oh.

42:51.735 --> 42:53.736
[GRUNTING]

42:57.157 --> 42:58.199
Hmm-hmm.

43:01.579 --> 43:02.620
Hah.

43:02.788 --> 43:03.955
[HUMS]

43:05.499 --> 43:06.624
Keep practicing.

43:06.834 --> 43:09.669
[YELLS]

43:09.837 --> 43:11.838
[GRUNTING]

43:16.927 --> 43:17.969
Take that.

43:24.268 --> 43:27.270
Hey, one of these guys must know
where they're holding Splinter.

43:27.438 --> 43:30.023
So don't knock them all out.

43:30.691 --> 43:32.942
I don't think that will be a problem, Leo.

43:44.163 --> 43:45.872
Gotcha.

43:48.667 --> 43:51.628
Hey, Donnie, Wheel of Fortune, dude.

43:57.092 --> 43:59.344
Bisen-tos. Now!

43:59.970 --> 44:01.012
[BOTH LAUGHING]

44:01.180 --> 44:02.764
I guess they're not game show fans.

44:02.931 --> 44:06.351
- And I thought everybody loved Vanna.
- Aah! Whoa!

44:10.522 --> 44:12.065
California roll. Ooh.

44:12.608 --> 44:14.233
Oh, what a spaz.

44:14.401 --> 44:16.736
- Missed again.
- Good thing they aren't lumberjacks.

44:16.904 --> 44:17.945
No joke.

44:18.113 --> 44:21.741
The only thing safe in the woods
would be the trees.

44:24.161 --> 44:27.622
Guys, I'm not so sure if this is,
structurally speaking...

44:27.790 --> 44:30.583
...such a good time
for your buddies to drop in.

44:34.755 --> 44:36.005
[FLOOR CREAKING]

44:36.173 --> 44:38.341
- Uh-oh.
BOTH: Aah!

44:40.928 --> 44:43.137
Oh, whoa. Wipeout.

44:43.305 --> 44:45.264
[TURTLES COUGHING]

44:48.894 --> 44:49.936
- Huh?
- Hmm?

44:50.646 --> 44:53.773
- Hmm.
- Oh, no.

44:56.193 --> 44:57.235
Mm.

44:57.403 --> 44:59.195
[ALL YELLING]

45:04.952 --> 45:08.037
Ha-ha. Ha-ha-ha-ha. Oh!

45:08.497 --> 45:10.456
Ooh. Ooh.

45:15.546 --> 45:16.796
Hey, hey, hey.

45:16.964 --> 45:18.131
[PIANO PLAYING RANDOM NOTES]

45:20.926 --> 45:22.260
Hai!

45:22.428 --> 45:24.804
[GRUNTING]

45:30.477 --> 45:31.936
[GASPS]

45:34.815 --> 45:38.484
Man, we could really use
Raph right about now.

45:43.157 --> 45:44.157
[CRASH]

45:44.324 --> 45:45.867
[GROWLING]

45:46.034 --> 45:47.952
Now what?

45:52.166 --> 45:56.878
Oh. You guys mind telling me what you're
doing to my little green pal over there?

45:57.045 --> 45:58.421
Mm?

45:59.173 --> 46:01.966
Oh, who is the babe?

46:02.134 --> 46:04.427
Who the heck is that?

46:04.595 --> 46:07.472
Wayne Gretzky on steroids?

46:08.182 --> 46:09.766
Attack.

46:09.933 --> 46:11.934
[ALL YELLING, GRUNTING]

46:18.567 --> 46:21.152
Aaa-aaa-aah!

46:26.825 --> 46:28.785
Come on, we got to get out of here.

46:35.000 --> 46:38.169
Help me. There used to be
a trapdoor here to the basement.

46:38.337 --> 46:40.171
Yeah, come on, you ugly muggers.

46:40.339 --> 46:41.964
Come on.

46:43.467 --> 46:45.468
We're getting out of here.

46:48.305 --> 46:51.224
CASEY: Gangway, men.
I'll take care of these guys.

46:54.061 --> 46:56.896
- You coming?
- I'll cover you.

46:57.272 --> 46:58.356
Good idea.

47:01.068 --> 47:02.318
[PHONE RINGS]

47:02.486 --> 47:04.070
APRIL [OVER MACHINE]:
Hi, this is April.

47:04.238 --> 47:06.030
- Leave a message after the beep.
CASEY: What?

47:06.740 --> 47:08.491
CHARLES:
April, it's Charles.

47:08.784 --> 47:11.369
I'm sorry.
I don't know how else to say this.

47:11.537 --> 47:12.662
You're fired, April.

47:12.830 --> 47:16.958
I'm sorry. I know this comes as a blow.

47:17.334 --> 47:20.169
- You can say that again, Chuck.
- Come on.

47:20.337 --> 47:22.255
Bye, guys, got to run.

47:22.422 --> 47:24.715
[NINJAS GRUNTING]

47:24.925 --> 47:26.175
[SIREN APPROACHING]

47:26.343 --> 47:28.427
Ninja, vanish.

47:36.061 --> 47:37.353
Oh.

47:37.938 --> 47:39.188
[SIRENS WAILING]

47:39.356 --> 47:41.357
[PANTING]

48:00.502 --> 48:02.503
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

48:06.133 --> 48:07.550
[GRUNTS]

48:09.845 --> 48:13.973
What are these freaks?

48:14.141 --> 48:17.268
How do they know how to fight like this?

48:19.771 --> 48:23.357
You will answer.

48:24.526 --> 48:28.154
Then hang there until you die.

48:42.294 --> 48:44.295
[YELLING, GRUNTING]

48:49.801 --> 48:51.802
[GRUNTING]

49:02.522 --> 49:04.815
Whoa.
Master Tatsu, stop, please, please.

49:04.983 --> 49:06.651
Please, no.

49:13.283 --> 49:16.702
Shinsho.

49:18.330 --> 49:20.623
You'll be all right. You'll be all right.

49:20.791 --> 49:23.793
[SHINSHO COUGHS, GROANS]

49:40.852 --> 49:45.773
How can a face so young
wear so many burdens?

49:45.941 --> 49:48.693
So you can talk.

49:48.860 --> 49:53.364
Yes, and I can also listen.

49:54.116 --> 49:58.077
Some say that the path
from inner turmoil...

49:58.245 --> 50:01.872
...begins with a friendly ear.

50:02.249 --> 50:04.583
My ear is open...

50:04.751 --> 50:08.879
...if you care to use it.
- No, I don't think so.

50:09.047 --> 50:11.007
What is your name?

50:12.759 --> 50:13.801
Danny.

50:13.969 --> 50:16.762
And have you no one to go to, Danny?

50:16.930 --> 50:18.055
No parent?

50:18.223 --> 50:20.516
My dad couldn't care less about me.

50:21.393 --> 50:23.936
I doubt that is true.

50:25.814 --> 50:27.273
Why?

50:28.442 --> 50:33.779
All fathers care for their sons.

50:41.163 --> 50:43.122
[CAR BACKFIRING]

50:43.290 --> 50:46.459
APRIL: How's Raphael?
LEONARDO: Not so good.

50:46.626 --> 50:49.170
CASEY: Hey, didn't they use this place
in The Grapes of Wrath?

50:49.337 --> 50:51.213
APRIL:
Very funny.

50:51.381 --> 50:54.925
I told you,
I haven't been up here in years.

50:55.135 --> 50:56.177
[SIGHS]

50:56.344 --> 50:58.345
[ENGINE STARTS]

50:58.513 --> 51:00.389
[CAR BACKFIRES THEN DIES]

51:01.516 --> 51:03.309
Can you fix it?

51:08.148 --> 51:09.315
[IMITATES GUNSHOT]

51:09.483 --> 51:11.025
Does that answer your question?

51:11.193 --> 51:14.487
I mean, the block's got a crack in it
the size of the San Andreas.

51:14.654 --> 51:16.322
- Wonderful.
- Ah.

51:17.324 --> 51:20.034
Well, I guess
I've got some walking to do.

51:20.202 --> 51:21.535
What for?

51:21.703 --> 51:24.121
Our nearest neighbor
is about four miles away.

51:24.289 --> 51:26.916
I need to get to a phone,
and I need to call my boss.

51:27.084 --> 51:28.501
You mean Charles?

51:28.668 --> 51:29.710
How did you know that?

51:29.878 --> 51:33.089
Well, he left a message on your machine
just before we got out.

51:33.256 --> 51:34.590
And?

51:35.884 --> 51:39.136
Well, hey, you just saved yourself
an eight-mile round-tripper.

51:39.888 --> 51:41.680
You were fired.

51:42.182 --> 51:43.682
I'm...

51:44.935 --> 51:46.477
- I just saved myself?
- Yeah.

51:46.645 --> 51:47.853
- Uh-oh.
APRIL: What did you do?

51:48.021 --> 51:50.314
Did you take classes in insensitivity?

51:50.482 --> 51:54.026
- I was just trying to break it to you easy.
- Oh, well, you failed miserably.

51:54.194 --> 51:57.404
Hey, Broadzilla, you wouldn't be here
if it werert for me, okay?

51:57.572 --> 52:00.199
Oh, and what do you want?
Do you want a thank you?

52:00.367 --> 52:03.702
No. It's me who should thank you
for that privilege, right?

52:03.870 --> 52:05.830
- Fine. Thank you.
- Yeah. No, thank you.

52:05.997 --> 52:08.791
- You're welcome.
- You're welcome.

52:10.502 --> 52:14.839
Gosh, it's kind of like Moonlighting,
isn't it?

52:15.006 --> 52:16.465
- Heh.
- Mm-hm.

52:16.716 --> 52:19.718
[HUMMING
"OLD MACDONALD HAD A FARM"

52:25.809 --> 52:28.394
APRIL [IN VOICEOVER]:
It's strange being back on the old farm.

52:28.562 --> 52:32.565
Even after all these years,
it still feels like home.

52:32.732 --> 52:36.569
My amazing new friends
have suffered their first real defeat.

52:36.736 --> 52:37.945
That's bad enough...

52:38.113 --> 52:41.657
...but they've also lost the opportunity
to find out about their mentor...

52:41.825 --> 52:45.286
...and I'm sure that hurts them
much more than anything else.

52:45.453 --> 52:48.914
Each of them deals with this confusion
in his own way.

52:49.082 --> 52:51.917
Donatello has found someone
to latch onto.

52:52.085 --> 52:55.171
CASEY:
Not even close, zip neck.

52:55.338 --> 52:58.924
The Professor and Mary Ann,
happily ever after.

52:59.092 --> 53:00.926
No way, atomic mouth.

53:01.094 --> 53:02.803
Gilligan was her main man.

53:02.971 --> 53:05.139
They'd be married
and have six kids by now.

53:05.307 --> 53:07.516
Gilligan was a geek, barfaroni.

53:07.684 --> 53:10.853
- You're the geek, camel breath.
- Dome head.

53:11.313 --> 53:12.855
Hmm!

53:13.064 --> 53:15.024
Elf lips.

53:16.109 --> 53:20.362
Let's give this a try,
see if this transplant worked, fungoid.

53:20.530 --> 53:23.616
- All right, here it goes. What are we on?
- Uh...

53:23.783 --> 53:24.992
- G.
- Heh.

53:25.160 --> 53:26.619
Here goes, gack face.

53:26.786 --> 53:28.913
I'm ready, hose brain.

53:29.956 --> 53:31.498
[ENGINE STARTS]

53:31.666 --> 53:34.084
[BOTH YELL]

53:34.669 --> 53:35.711
[WOOD CLATTERS]

53:37.464 --> 53:41.008
It worked. Uh... Hey.

53:42.302 --> 53:46.639
APRIL: Leonardo, meanwhile,
has kept a constant vigil with Raphael.

54:22.008 --> 54:24.343
APRIL:
He'll be okay.

54:29.599 --> 54:31.350
And then there's Casey Jones...

54:31.518 --> 54:33.811
...a 9-year-old trapped in a mars body.

54:33.979 --> 54:37.815
He might almost be cute
if it wasrt for that pigheadedness.

54:38.566 --> 54:40.150
Donatello.

54:40.318 --> 54:41.986
He's out with the others...

54:42.153 --> 54:44.613
...they're exercising.

54:44.781 --> 54:46.907
Doing something together, I don't know.

54:47.325 --> 54:48.993
You want some help?

54:50.078 --> 54:53.956
- Ah.
- Hey, I am your man. I am Mr. Fix-it.

54:54.374 --> 54:55.708
All right.

54:55.875 --> 54:58.585
- Let's go.
- Lead the way, toots.

55:00.171 --> 55:03.048
- Toots?
- Oh... Babe?

55:04.342 --> 55:05.884
Sweetcakes?

55:06.886 --> 55:09.555
Ah! Princess.

55:09.764 --> 55:12.099
Do you want to throw me a clue here?
I'm drowning.

55:12.267 --> 55:14.226
You know what? That's okay.

55:14.394 --> 55:17.021
- I'll take care of it myself.
- Fine, that's up to you.

55:17.188 --> 55:20.190
Just don't come around here
asking for my help anymore.

55:20.358 --> 55:22.067
See, I wouldn't ask for your help...

55:22.235 --> 55:26.905
...if you were the last thing
on the face of this planet.

55:27.615 --> 55:29.742
It's coming along nicely.

55:35.206 --> 55:36.707
[SNORING]

55:36.875 --> 55:38.584
RAPHAEL: Hey.
- What?

55:39.044 --> 55:40.753
[MOANS]

55:40.920 --> 55:42.254
Raph.

55:42.422 --> 55:45.257
You're awake. How do you feel?

55:45.717 --> 55:49.803
What's a guy got to do
to get some food around here?

55:49.971 --> 55:52.264
Hey. Hey, he's awake.

55:52.432 --> 55:53.974
He wants some food.

55:54.142 --> 55:56.518
Bring some food.

55:56.686 --> 55:58.812
You're gonna be okay, Raph.

55:58.980 --> 56:00.481
You're gonna be okay.

56:00.648 --> 56:02.858
Yeah, yeah, all right, Leo.

56:03.026 --> 56:05.110
Get a grip, will you?

56:05.278 --> 56:06.612
Listen, Raph.

56:07.364 --> 56:08.405
[GRUNTS]

56:08.573 --> 56:10.783
About what I said before...

56:12.619 --> 56:13.702
...you know...

56:13.870 --> 56:16.789
...about not needing you and all, like...

56:17.165 --> 56:18.582
Leo...

56:18.750 --> 56:20.292
...don't.

56:20.460 --> 56:23.045
Oh, boy, we missed you.

56:23.213 --> 56:24.254
[SNIFFLES]

56:24.422 --> 56:26.131
It's a Kodak moment.

56:26.299 --> 56:29.218
[APRIL AND DONATELLO LAUGH]

56:33.848 --> 56:34.890
[ALL GRUNTING]

56:35.058 --> 56:37.226
APRIL:
The turtles are four once again...

56:37.394 --> 56:39.144
...and yet, still not whole.

56:40.438 --> 56:42.898
A lingering doubt remains.

56:43.066 --> 56:45.776
An unknown
which they can't bear to face...

56:46.194 --> 56:48.237
...their greatest fear.

56:48.405 --> 56:51.824
Splinter!

56:53.493 --> 56:55.994
[MOANS]

56:57.205 --> 57:00.040
TATSU:
Your empire flourishes, Master Shredder.

57:00.208 --> 57:02.835
MAN: No, no, no, that's a stereo.
SHREDDER: What more from the rat?

57:03.002 --> 57:04.002
TATSU:
Nothing.

57:04.170 --> 57:05.963
He will not speak.

57:06.131 --> 57:08.507
SHREDDER:
And the boy who led us to the turtles?

57:08.675 --> 57:11.343
He is still missing.

57:11.636 --> 57:13.679
I do not understand.

57:13.847 --> 57:16.723
Why do the turtles trouble you, master?

57:16.891 --> 57:19.601
They have not been seen for many days.

57:19.769 --> 57:25.149
Something about the way
you described their fighting.

57:25.316 --> 57:28.402
Something familiar.

57:29.612 --> 57:31.196
Something...

57:32.824 --> 57:36.076
...from the past.

57:39.122 --> 57:41.123
[GRUNTING, YELLING]

58:06.816 --> 58:08.817
[RADIO PLAYING POP MUSIC]

58:11.070 --> 58:12.446
[APRIL GROANS]

58:27.879 --> 58:29.505
[SIGHS]

58:33.801 --> 58:35.093
[MOANS]

58:35.261 --> 58:37.387
[GROANS]

58:39.766 --> 58:41.266
[CHUCKLES]

58:44.604 --> 58:46.063
APRIL: Ointment?
- Mm-mm.

58:46.481 --> 58:47.523
Hey, guys.

58:47.690 --> 58:49.107
[HUMS, CHUCKLES]

58:49.275 --> 58:50.275
Hmm.

58:50.443 --> 58:52.110
[SNICKERING]

58:53.071 --> 58:55.072
Oh, God.

58:55.823 --> 58:57.699
Funny, Mikey.

59:19.722 --> 59:21.557
Leonardo.

59:22.016 --> 59:24.142
Hah. Splinter.

59:24.602 --> 59:28.730
What Russian novel,
embracing more than 500 characters...

59:28.898 --> 59:31.149
...is set in the Napoleonic Wars?

59:31.317 --> 59:32.317
War and Peace.

59:32.652 --> 59:34.236
He's alive.

59:34.404 --> 59:35.612
- Hey.
- Thanks, spaz.

59:35.780 --> 59:37.656
Splinter's alive.

59:37.824 --> 59:39.825
We know, Leo. Of course he is.

59:39.993 --> 59:41.326
We all think he's alive.

59:41.494 --> 59:43.495
I don't think.

59:43.663 --> 59:45.330
- I know.
- Huh?

59:45.498 --> 59:46.540
Huh?

59:48.668 --> 59:51.795
[BLOWING]

59:52.338 --> 59:53.964
Leo...

59:54.340 --> 59:57.092
...if you dragged us
out here for nothing...

59:57.260 --> 59:59.678
Don't worry. I came prepared.

59:59.846 --> 01:00:01.096
- Put those away.
- Heh-heh.

01:00:01.264 --> 01:00:02.472
Heh.

01:00:04.142 --> 01:00:07.686
Now, everybody close your eyes
and concentrate.

01:00:07.854 --> 01:00:10.022
Concentrate hard.

01:00:12.191 --> 01:00:15.277
[SIGHS, ANIMALS HOWLING]

01:00:36.549 --> 01:00:40.510
SPLINTER:
I am proud of you, my sons.

01:00:40.678 --> 01:00:43.180
Tonight you have learned...

01:00:43.348 --> 01:00:48.101
...the final and greatest truth
of the ninja...

01:00:48.269 --> 01:00:53.649
...that ultimate mastery
comes not of the body...

01:00:53.816 --> 01:00:56.193
...but of the mind.

01:00:56.361 --> 01:01:01.823
Together, there is nothing
your four minds cannot accomplish.

01:01:01.991 --> 01:01:03.116
Help each other.

01:01:03.284 --> 01:01:05.911
Draw upon one another.

01:01:06.079 --> 01:01:11.917
And always remember
the true force that binds you...

01:01:12.085 --> 01:01:16.797
...the same as that
which brought me here tonight...

01:01:16.964 --> 01:01:23.011
...that which I gladly return
with my final words.

01:01:23.304 --> 01:01:26.515
I love you all, my sons.

01:01:33.314 --> 01:01:36.483
Huh. Huh? Uh... Huh.

01:01:36.776 --> 01:01:38.777
[SNIFFLING]

01:01:54.961 --> 01:01:57.254
[ROOSTER CROWS]

01:02:05.263 --> 01:02:08.056
So you actually played professionally?

01:02:08.224 --> 01:02:11.601
Before I got hurt, less than a year.

01:02:13.521 --> 01:02:14.980
I'm sorry.

01:02:15.148 --> 01:02:16.982
- So was I.
- Ah-ah-ahem.

01:02:20.319 --> 01:02:21.737
Guys, I told you...

01:02:21.904 --> 01:02:24.489
...I hate it when you do that, all right?

01:02:25.408 --> 01:02:26.992
What is it?

01:02:27.493 --> 01:02:30.078
It's time to go back.

01:02:49.932 --> 01:02:54.269
APRIL:
Oh, no. Oh.

01:02:54.437 --> 01:02:55.937
- Home sweet home.
APRIL: Ha-ha.

01:02:56.105 --> 01:02:57.147
Yuch.

01:02:57.815 --> 01:03:00.275
I know what it's like to travel
without a green card.

01:03:00.443 --> 01:03:01.526
This isn't bad.

01:03:01.694 --> 01:03:04.196
Nice place, guys. In fact, I...

01:03:04.363 --> 01:03:05.405
[MANHOLE COVER OPENS]

01:03:05.573 --> 01:03:07.616
Are you coming or not, dude?

01:03:10.870 --> 01:03:11.995
[GROANS]

01:03:12.205 --> 01:03:13.914
CASEY:
This is great, it's great.

01:03:14.081 --> 01:03:17.375
First it's the farm that time forgot,
and now this.

01:03:17.543 --> 01:03:20.629
Why don't I ever fall in
with people who own condos?

01:03:21.506 --> 01:03:24.883
Guess it's hard to get
good maid service in a sewer.

01:03:25.551 --> 01:03:27.427
Maybe you guys should try Roto-Rooter.

01:03:27.595 --> 01:03:30.222
APRIL: Would you quit complaining?
It's just for the night.

01:03:30.389 --> 01:03:33.225
I still don't see
why we don't get started right away.

01:03:33.392 --> 01:03:35.143
It's been a long drive, Raph.

01:03:35.311 --> 01:03:38.230
And before we go out advertising
to The Foot that we're back...

01:03:38.397 --> 01:03:41.066
...we could all use a few hours' sleep.
RAPHAEL: Yeah.

01:03:41.234 --> 01:03:44.402
I know, you're right. I'm just...
What's that?

01:03:44.570 --> 01:03:46.071
[CLATTERING]

01:03:46.405 --> 01:03:47.864
[GROWLING]

01:03:48.032 --> 01:03:49.491
APRIL: Danny?
- Don't shoot.

01:03:49.659 --> 01:03:52.244
- I don't think it's loaded, kid.
- Danny...

01:03:52.411 --> 01:03:53.787
...what are you doing here?

01:03:53.955 --> 01:03:56.248
MICHAELANGELO: Where'd he come from?
DONATELLO: Beats me.

01:03:56.415 --> 01:03:57.958
I ran away from home.

01:03:58.125 --> 01:04:01.503
APRIL: Oh, God,
your father's gonna have kittens.

01:04:01.671 --> 01:04:03.588
- Does this thing work?
- No.

01:04:03.756 --> 01:04:05.549
No, please don't call.

01:04:05.716 --> 01:04:07.676
Just let me stay here the night with you.

01:04:07.844 --> 01:04:09.594
We can call in the morning. I promise.

01:04:09.762 --> 01:04:12.264
- Danny, listen, your dad, he's...
- Hold on, hold it.

01:04:12.431 --> 01:04:17.060
Okay, now, what is all this talk
about spending the night down here?

01:04:17.353 --> 01:04:19.354
You're a claustrophobic.

01:04:19.981 --> 01:04:21.773
[CHUCKLES]

01:04:21.941 --> 01:04:24.276
- Do you want a fist in the mouth?
- Mm-mm.

01:04:24.443 --> 01:04:26.528
I've never even looked
at another guy before.

01:04:26.696 --> 01:04:30.824
What he means is that
you're afraid of enclosed areas.

01:04:31.450 --> 01:04:33.118
Afraid?

01:04:34.912 --> 01:04:38.331
- What, me? Is that what you think?
- Mm-hm.

01:04:39.166 --> 01:04:43.795
Ah. Hey, I don't have to take this stuff
about being afraid.

01:04:44.005 --> 01:04:46.631
[CLANGING]

01:04:46.883 --> 01:04:49.134
I'm gonna sleep in the truck.

01:04:52.346 --> 01:04:56.975
[LAUGHING]

01:04:57.143 --> 01:04:59.686
DANNY:
Jeez, these are good.

01:04:59.854 --> 01:05:00.979
APRIL:
Thanks.

01:05:01.147 --> 01:05:02.981
DANNY:
Do you think maybe I could have one?

01:05:03.441 --> 01:05:05.317
- Sure, why not?
- Thanks.

01:05:05.484 --> 01:05:06.484
[YAWNS]

01:05:06.652 --> 01:05:08.069
Oh, man, I could really go...

01:05:08.237 --> 01:05:10.697
...for a little deep-dish action
right about now.

01:05:10.865 --> 01:05:13.241
I had some pizza down here
the other day.

01:05:13.409 --> 01:05:15.493
- There might be some left over.
- Mm? Mm? Uh-huh.

01:05:15.745 --> 01:05:17.329
- Wa-ah. Wa-ah-aah!
- Ha-ha-ha.

01:05:18.289 --> 01:05:19.331
[HUMS]

01:05:19.498 --> 01:05:21.499
- Well?
- Question.

01:05:21.667 --> 01:05:25.503
- Yeah?
- Do you like penicillin on your pizza?

01:05:25.671 --> 01:05:27.839
Oh! Ugh.

01:05:28.007 --> 01:05:30.008
[BOTH HUMMING "TAPS"]

01:05:39.018 --> 01:05:41.645
"Afraid of enclosed areas."

01:05:41.812 --> 01:05:43.980
[SCOFFS]

01:06:06.212 --> 01:06:08.755
[TURTLES SNORING]

01:06:08.965 --> 01:06:10.715
SHREDDER [IN VOICEOVER]:
You are here...

01:06:10.883 --> 01:06:14.386
...because the outside world rejects you.

01:06:14.553 --> 01:06:17.097
And you have no one to go to, Danny?

01:06:17.264 --> 01:06:18.974
This is your family.

01:06:19.141 --> 01:06:22.811
SPLINTER:
All fathers care for their sons.

01:06:22.979 --> 01:06:25.230
[GASPS]

01:06:41.872 --> 01:06:43.415
[MANHOLE COVER SLIDES]

01:06:51.424 --> 01:06:53.425
[OPENS CAR DOOR]

01:07:24.874 --> 01:07:26.875
[INDISTINCT CHATTER, LAUGHTER]

01:07:33.466 --> 01:07:34.632
BOY 1:
Nice shot, man.

01:07:35.259 --> 01:07:37.093
BOY 2:
I need a cigar.

01:07:37.261 --> 01:07:39.596
Where is my cigar?

01:07:45.061 --> 01:07:46.978
BOY 3:
Hey.

01:07:47.146 --> 01:07:49.647
Great how you did that, it rocks.

01:07:57.323 --> 01:07:58.782
[MOANS SOFTLY]

01:08:00.367 --> 01:08:03.828
I have not seen you for days.

01:08:04.789 --> 01:08:08.666
Yeah, I've been down at my hideout
a lot lately.

01:08:09.168 --> 01:08:14.380
And do you now hide
from your surrogate family as well?

01:08:16.675 --> 01:08:18.259
I don't know.

01:08:18.719 --> 01:08:20.345
I too...

01:08:20.513 --> 01:08:23.014
...once had a family, Danny.

01:08:24.308 --> 01:08:26.184
Many years ago...

01:08:26.352 --> 01:08:28.728
...I lived in Japan...

01:08:28.895 --> 01:08:31.773
...a pet of my master, Yoshi...

01:08:31.941 --> 01:08:34.776
...mimicking his movements
from my cage...

01:08:34.944 --> 01:08:39.531
...and learning
the mysterious art of Ninjitsu...

01:08:39.698 --> 01:08:44.536
...for Yoshi was one of Japars
finest shadow warriors.

01:08:44.703 --> 01:08:50.375
His only rival was
a man named Oroku Saki...

01:08:50.542 --> 01:08:53.670
...and they competed in all things...

01:08:53.837 --> 01:08:59.634
...but none more fiercely
than for the love of a woman.

01:08:59.801 --> 01:09:01.928
Tang Shen.

01:09:02.846 --> 01:09:06.140
Shers love was only for my master...

01:09:06.308 --> 01:09:09.352
...and rather than see him
fight Saki for her hand...

01:09:09.520 --> 01:09:11.229
...she persuaded Yoshi...

01:09:11.397 --> 01:09:14.064
...to flee with me to America...

01:09:14.233 --> 01:09:16.734
...but Saki vowed vengeance.

01:09:16.902 --> 01:09:19.069
I remember it well.

01:09:19.238 --> 01:09:21.738
As my master returned home...

01:09:21.907 --> 01:09:25.785
...to find his beloved Shen
lying on the floor.

01:09:26.245 --> 01:09:28.537
And then he saw her killer.

01:09:28.872 --> 01:09:32.250
Saki wasted no words,
and during the struggle...

01:09:32.417 --> 01:09:33.751
...my cage was broken.

01:09:34.086 --> 01:09:37.337
I leapt to Saki's face,
biting and clawing...

01:09:37.506 --> 01:09:39.256
...but he threw me to the floor...

01:09:39.425 --> 01:09:43.011
...and took one swipe with his katana,
slicing my ear.

01:09:44.555 --> 01:09:48.765
Then he was gone and I was alone.

01:09:50.978 --> 01:09:55.481
Whatever happened to this Oroku Saki?

01:09:55.900 --> 01:09:58.651
No one really knows...

01:09:58.819 --> 01:10:03.781
...but you wear his symbol
upon your brow.

01:10:22.384 --> 01:10:23.718
[MAN GRUNTS]

01:10:34.855 --> 01:10:37.148
SHREDDER:
What are you doing in there, boy?

01:10:37.316 --> 01:10:38.816
Nothing.

01:10:48.661 --> 01:10:50.453
Where have you been?

01:10:50.996 --> 01:10:52.830
DANNY:
Nowhere.

01:10:53.332 --> 01:10:55.166
You're lying to me.

01:10:55.334 --> 01:10:58.795
- No.
- And you're hiding something as well.

01:10:59.004 --> 01:11:00.421
Shaah!

01:11:25.197 --> 01:11:27.865
They're back.

01:11:30.953 --> 01:11:32.954
TATSU:
Master.

01:11:33.122 --> 01:11:36.165
There will be no mistake this time.

01:11:36.333 --> 01:11:38.042
I go myself.

01:11:38.585 --> 01:11:40.128
And the rat...

01:11:40.879 --> 01:11:42.380
...kill it.

01:11:43.716 --> 01:11:44.841
MAN:
Come on, men.

01:11:49.096 --> 01:11:51.556
- Hey, what do you want?
- Shh, shh.

01:11:51.724 --> 01:11:52.974
Recognize me now, kid?

01:11:53.142 --> 01:11:55.727
- Hey, what's the deal?
- You got to come with me.

01:11:55.894 --> 01:12:00.148
- What are you talking about come with you?
- They're gonna kill Splinter.

01:12:06.655 --> 01:12:07.822
[GRUNTING]

01:12:22.588 --> 01:12:24.589
[ALL YELLING]

01:12:37.478 --> 01:12:39.479
[TURTLES YELLING]

01:12:46.945 --> 01:12:49.072
DONATELLO:
Hee-hee-hee. No sweat.

01:12:50.449 --> 01:12:54.118
Gosh, I do hope there's more of them.

01:12:56.622 --> 01:12:58.164
[PANTING, GRUNTING]

01:12:58.332 --> 01:12:59.874
- Huh?
- Ah.

01:13:00.042 --> 01:13:02.085
Good.

01:13:10.469 --> 01:13:12.470
Well, where are the keys?

01:13:15.474 --> 01:13:18.142
Who are you?

01:13:18.394 --> 01:13:19.685
Hey.

01:13:21.397 --> 01:13:24.148
- Ahh.
- The name's Casey Jones.

01:13:26.360 --> 01:13:27.944
A friend.

01:13:28.195 --> 01:13:29.570
[GROANS]

01:13:33.075 --> 01:13:34.826
Let's get out of here.

01:13:34.993 --> 01:13:36.160
[TATSU GRUNTS]

01:13:39.039 --> 01:13:41.040
[GRUNTING, YELLING]

01:13:52.970 --> 01:13:55.096
A little to the right. A little to the left.

01:13:55.556 --> 01:13:57.098
One more time.

01:13:57.266 --> 01:13:59.350
A little bit more like that.

01:13:59.518 --> 01:14:01.352
And stop. Perfect.

01:14:02.479 --> 01:14:03.521
Aah!

01:14:03.689 --> 01:14:06.315
- You're a natural, sis.
- Thanks.

01:14:06.567 --> 01:14:08.151
Ha! Ha-ha! Ha!

01:14:09.445 --> 01:14:14.490
[GRUNTS]

01:14:14.658 --> 01:14:20.329
Now, you know, a little Primatene
might just help to clear that up there.

01:14:22.624 --> 01:14:24.625
That's gonna cost you, Tinker Bell.

01:14:26.420 --> 01:14:29.213
I don't think that you're listening.

01:14:35.554 --> 01:14:41.934
You know, I'm starting to pick up
on a little language barrier thing going here.

01:14:57.868 --> 01:15:00.870
[TATSU GROANING]

01:15:02.748 --> 01:15:03.915
Fore.

01:15:10.380 --> 01:15:12.381
[PANTING]

01:15:13.800 --> 01:15:16.719
I'll never call golf a dull game again.

01:15:16.887 --> 01:15:18.888
[GRUNTING]

01:15:21.850 --> 01:15:24.018
Gangway.

01:15:35.781 --> 01:15:37.782
Showoff.

01:15:38.784 --> 01:15:41.702
What are we just standing here for?
Let's get him.

01:15:44.456 --> 01:15:47.124
Do you want to be first, junior, huh?

01:15:47.292 --> 01:15:48.960
We have a loyalty to The Shredder.

01:15:49.336 --> 01:15:50.962
The Shredder uses you.

01:15:51.630 --> 01:15:55.633
He poisons your minds
to obtain that which he desires.

01:15:57.761 --> 01:16:02.557
He cares nothing for you
or the people you hurt.

01:16:03.976 --> 01:16:05.226
We're a family.

01:16:05.394 --> 01:16:06.811
[CROWD MURMURING]

01:16:06.979 --> 01:16:10.398
Family? Is that what you said? Family?

01:16:11.358 --> 01:16:14.443
You call this here...

01:16:14.611 --> 01:16:16.779
...and that down there, family?

01:16:17.864 --> 01:16:19.865
[CROWD MURMURING]

01:16:26.832 --> 01:16:28.541
[EXHALES]

01:16:29.209 --> 01:16:31.335
Casey.

01:16:36.925 --> 01:16:38.926
[CROWD WHISPERING]

01:16:45.851 --> 01:16:47.852
[NINJAS YELLING, GRUNTING]

01:16:54.192 --> 01:16:56.485
DONATELLO:
Hey, dudes, where you going?

01:16:56.695 --> 01:16:57.820
Hai!

01:16:57.988 --> 01:17:01.991
Ha! Hey, Donnie, looks like this one's
suffering from shell shock. Ha!

01:17:02.200 --> 01:17:03.784
Hmm. Too derivative.

01:17:04.036 --> 01:17:05.369
[YELLS]

01:17:05.537 --> 01:17:08.164
Boy, I guess we can really shell it out.

01:17:08.332 --> 01:17:10.207
Too cliché.

01:17:11.168 --> 01:17:14.211
Well, it was a shell of a good hit.

01:17:14.379 --> 01:17:17.256
I like it. Step up.

01:17:18.508 --> 01:17:21.677
Awesome. Ha! Ha! Ha!

01:17:21.845 --> 01:17:22.887
[LAUGHS]

01:17:23.472 --> 01:17:26.140
Hey, where do you think you're going?

01:17:30.812 --> 01:17:31.896
NINJA: Hey.
- Hmm.

01:17:32.064 --> 01:17:34.398
Hey, wait for me.

01:17:34.733 --> 01:17:36.776
Whoop! Yaah!

01:17:36.943 --> 01:17:40.112
God, I love being a turtle!

01:17:40.280 --> 01:17:43.115
[YELLS]

01:17:51.166 --> 01:17:53.459
Ha-ha! Yee-ha!

01:17:59.049 --> 01:18:00.591
Oh!

01:18:00.759 --> 01:18:06.055
Come on, come on.

01:18:06.390 --> 01:18:07.890
[GRUNTING, YELLING]

01:18:25.617 --> 01:18:27.785
Aw. No more?

01:18:39.297 --> 01:18:40.548
Nyah. Nyak-nyak.

01:18:41.550 --> 01:18:45.970
Does anybody have any idea
about who or what this is?

01:18:46.138 --> 01:18:47.430
I don't know...

01:18:47.597 --> 01:18:49.765
...but I'll bet it never has to look
for a can opener.

01:18:49.933 --> 01:18:50.975
[CHUCKLES]

01:18:51.977 --> 01:18:56.147
You fight well in the old style...

01:18:56.314 --> 01:18:58.816
...but you've caused me enough trouble.

01:18:59.568 --> 01:19:02.111
Now you face...

01:19:02.279 --> 01:19:03.779
...The Shredder.

01:19:04.740 --> 01:19:06.741
- The Shredder? Heh.
- Uh...

01:19:06.908 --> 01:19:09.535
Maybe all that hardware's
for making coleslaw.

01:19:10.120 --> 01:19:11.662
I got him.

01:19:13.248 --> 01:19:17.585
[GROWLS, GRUNTING]

01:19:17.753 --> 01:19:19.795
- This guy's good.
- Yeah.

01:19:19.963 --> 01:19:22.173
- Why don't you go next?
- Thank you.

01:19:22.340 --> 01:19:24.008
[YELLS]

01:19:26.636 --> 01:19:29.513
Uh... Match you for it?

01:19:30.807 --> 01:19:32.808
BOTH:
One, two, three. Mm.

01:19:32.976 --> 01:19:34.685
- Damn.
- Great. Wah!

01:19:35.520 --> 01:19:37.271
[TURTLES GRUNTING IN DISTANCE]

01:19:37.439 --> 01:19:38.856
Come on.

01:19:42.694 --> 01:19:44.695
[CROWD MURMURING]

01:19:45.655 --> 01:19:48.073
So much for family, huh?

01:19:49.868 --> 01:19:52.495
TEEN:
Yeah, I'm just so hungry, you know.

01:19:52.704 --> 01:19:54.038
[PANTING]

01:19:54.206 --> 01:19:55.331
Now...

01:19:55.499 --> 01:19:57.708
...at exactly what point...

01:19:57.876 --> 01:19:59.960
...did we lose control here?

01:20:00.128 --> 01:20:04.048
Maybe somebody ought to tell him
that we're the good guys.

01:20:04.216 --> 01:20:05.508
- Yeah.
- Any thoughts?

01:20:05.675 --> 01:20:07.551
I've only got one thought.

01:20:07.719 --> 01:20:09.887
This guy knows where Splinter is.

01:20:12.390 --> 01:20:14.058
[ALL YELLING, GRUNTING]

01:20:14.810 --> 01:20:17.228
Looks like your boys
are going to need a little...

01:20:19.064 --> 01:20:20.439
Where did he go?

01:20:39.918 --> 01:20:41.544
Oh, boy.

01:20:41.711 --> 01:20:43.629
Leftovers.

01:20:54.724 --> 01:20:55.766
[ENGINE STARTS]

01:20:58.937 --> 01:21:00.688
Yee-ha!

01:21:11.366 --> 01:21:13.117
It's a talent.

01:21:24.129 --> 01:21:25.629
[GROANS]

01:21:26.798 --> 01:21:28.799
[PANTING]

01:21:29.801 --> 01:21:31.552
Where's Splinter?

01:21:32.679 --> 01:21:36.223
- Ah. The rat, so it has a name.
- Huh?

01:21:37.976 --> 01:21:39.476
It had a name.

01:21:40.145 --> 01:21:41.812
[GRUNTS]

01:21:41.980 --> 01:21:43.314
You lie.

01:21:45.317 --> 01:21:47.318
Do I?

01:21:47.485 --> 01:21:51.280
[YELLS]

01:21:51.990 --> 01:21:53.324
[GROANS]

01:21:53.825 --> 01:21:54.950
[GASPS]

01:21:55.118 --> 01:21:56.160
He dies.

01:21:56.453 --> 01:21:59.830
- Huh?
- Weapons.

01:22:02.000 --> 01:22:05.127
- Now.
- Oh.

01:22:05.754 --> 01:22:07.963
[GRUNTS]

01:22:12.928 --> 01:22:14.887
Fools. Ha-ha.

01:22:15.055 --> 01:22:19.350
The three of you might have
overpowered me with the loss of but one.

01:22:19.935 --> 01:22:24.021
Now your fate will be his.

01:22:24.189 --> 01:22:25.606
ALL:
No.

01:22:27.067 --> 01:22:28.108
SHREDDER:
Oh.

01:22:28.276 --> 01:22:30.069
Splinter.

01:22:31.571 --> 01:22:35.199
- Aah.
- Yes, Oroku Saki.

01:22:35.367 --> 01:22:37.368
I know who you are.

01:22:38.495 --> 01:22:41.372
We met many years ago...

01:22:41.665 --> 01:22:44.458
...in the home of my master...

01:22:44.626 --> 01:22:46.126
...Hamato Yoshi.

01:22:52.717 --> 01:22:54.551
It's him.

01:22:56.096 --> 01:22:58.806
You.

01:23:00.016 --> 01:23:04.853
Now I will finish
what I began with your ear.

01:23:05.605 --> 01:23:11.193
[YELLS]

01:23:12.821 --> 01:23:14.488
[SHREDDER GRUNTS, GROANS]

01:23:14.656 --> 01:23:17.032
[CROWD CHATTERING]

01:23:17.909 --> 01:23:21.704
Death comes for us all, Oroku Saki...

01:23:21.871 --> 01:23:25.082
...but something much worse
comes for you.

01:23:25.250 --> 01:23:27.751
For when you die, it will be...

01:23:30.088 --> 01:23:33.549
[SCREAMS]

01:23:37.721 --> 01:23:39.596
- Without honor.

01:23:40.724 --> 01:23:42.141
Oops.

01:23:51.443 --> 01:23:54.403
- Splinter, are you okay?
- Oh, Splinter.

01:23:54.738 --> 01:23:57.156
Oh, Splinter, we were so worried.

01:23:57.323 --> 01:23:58.615
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

01:23:58.783 --> 01:23:59.783
Kids.

01:23:59.951 --> 01:24:01.952
[CHUCKLES]

